OL,3,CSNP Westminster leader demands urgent
OL,4,Creview of UK's 'anti-business policies'
OL,6,FArguing that Labour's policies are
OL,7,F"destroying jobs, squeezing wages,
OL,8,Fincreasing prices and harming
OL,9,Finvestment across Scotland and the
OL,10,FUK", Mr Doogan vowed: "As the SNP's
OL,11,FWestminster leader, I will be an
OL,12,Funashamedly pro-business voice in the
OL,13,FUK Parliament ` championing support
OL,14,Ffor our business community to create
OL,15,Fgood local jobs, boost people's wages,
OL,16,Fdeliver investment in our communities
OL,17,Fand bring wealth back into our economy.
OL,26,@oD@AOUrD@CO]rD@WOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1779066195
OL,3,CSNP Westminster leader demands urgent
OL,4,Creview of UK's 'anti-business policies'
OL,6,F"Family businesses, and key
OL,7,Findustries, are at the beating heart
OL,8,Fof our communities ` from the corner
OL,9,Fshop and local pub, to farming and
OL,10,Ffishing, and Scotland's crucial energy
OL,11,Fsector."
OL,13,FHe said that "Britain's broken economy
OL,14,Fstill hasn't revived from the 2008
OL,15,Ffinancial crash", with the MP adding
OL,16,Fthat the UK had seen "20 years of
OL,17,Fstagnation" with "poor wages, rising
OL,18,Fliving costs, flatlining economic
OL,19,Fgrowth, low productivity and the self-
OL,20,Finflicted disaster of Brexit".
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@HO]uD@NOUwD@PO]xD@VOUyD@KO]yD@
OL,26,AROU|D@]O]
